        "timestamp": "2017-07-24 20:57:03.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Verified-1\n\nAAI-57 says that the auth library will be part of the gizmo repo, is this intended for aai-common?  Should the story be changed?",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
      {
        "id": "006bbf0dcef2b36b09baf0dfec3226b175b2553f",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 453,
          "name": "Steven Blimkie",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "steven.blimkie@amdocs.com",
          "username": "sblimkie"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2017-07-24 21:08:52.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 4: Code-Review+1\n\n> AAI-57 says that the auth library will be part of the gizmo repo,\n > is this intended for aai-common?  Should the story be changed?\n\nThe auth library is going to be used by Gizmo, but it is intended as a common library which can also be used by other services.\n\nBased on the the thread on the discussion group, the consensus seemed to be that we wanted to put this type of library into the aai-common repository.\n\nSo yes, maybe the wording in AAI-57 needs to be changed.",
        "patchset_number": 4
      },
